Deploy azure resources using arm templates

 Steps Followed to Deploy the Storage Account
Created a new folder in local system to organize the project files:

bash
Copy
Edit
mkdir dummy3
cd dummy3
Created an ARM template named storage-account.json with the following structure:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "$schema": "https://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/2019-04-01/deploymentTemplate.json#",
  "contentVersion": "1.0.0.0",
  "resources": [
    {
      "type": "Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts",
      "apiVersion": "2023-05-01",
      "name": "shabeerstore2025",
      "location": "[resourceGroup().location]",
      "kind": "StorageV2",
      "sku": {
        "name": "Premium_LRS",
        "tier": "Premium"
      }
    }
  ]
}
Logged in to Azure via CLI:

bash
Copy
Edit
az login
Verified existing Resource Group or created one if not available:

bash
Copy
Edit
az group list --output table
